EXTREMECRAFT COMMANDS

==================================================
IN-GAME COMMANDS (Forge Runtime)
==================================================

Root: /ec

/ec debug
/ec validate                      (requires permission level 2)
/ec dump_registry                 (requires permission level 2)
/ec modules

/ec ability test <ability>
/ec ability give <ability>

/ec xp give <amount>
/ec skill unlock <node>
/ec level set <level>

/ec spell cast <spell>
/ec mana set <value>
/ec class set <class>

/ec machine debug

/ec reload                        (requires permission level 2)
/ec reload_data                   (requires permission level 2)

/ec debug_screen


Root: /extremecraft

/extremecraft level get
/extremecraft level set <value>   (requires permission level 2)

/extremecraft class list
/extremecraft class set <id>

/extremecraft quest list
/extremecraft quest claim <id>


==================================================
ASSET / TOOLING COMMANDS
==================================================

Primary generator:
.\.venv\Scripts\python tools/generate_assets.py --materials --export-blockbench --preview

Asset Studio CLI:
python assetstudio.py --help
python assetstudio.py generate tool mythril_pickaxe
python assetstudio.py generate material mythril
python assetstudio.py generate ore mythril
python assetstudio.py import blockbench workspace\blockbench\mythril_pickaxe.bbmodel
python assetstudio.py export blockbench mythril_pickaxe --kind item
python assetstudio.py scan-registry
python assetstudio.py validate
python assetstudio.py project init --name extremecraft-assets
python assetstudio.py project build --target datapack
python assetstudio.py skilltree new demo_tree
python assetstudio.py skilltree list
python assetstudio.py skilltree validate demo_tree
python assetstudio.py skilltree export demo_tree --out workspace\exports\demo_tree.json
python assetstudio.py skilltree import workspace\exports\demo_tree.json
python assetstudio.py --gui

Pip setup:
pip install -e .
pip install -e .[core]
pip install -e .[gui]
pip install -e .[all]